   "description": "Bror Gustaf Melcher Hakansson was a Swedish clergyman born on July 18, 1897 in Gothenburg. He was the son of property owner Gustaf H. and Hanna Bergström, and was married to Gerd Andersson in 1935. They had three children: Ingrid, Bertil, and Margareta. Bror Hakansson graduated from Gothenburg High School in 1918 and received his Bachelor of Arts in Theology from the Theological Seminary in 1921. He passed practical theological exams in 1927 and was ordained as a priest in the Gothenburg Diocese in 1928. Bror Hakansson served as vicar in Berghem, Dalstorp, Västra Frölunda, Mölndal, and Skredsvik, as well as a curate in Starrkärr and a church administrative assistant in Carl Johans församling in Gothenburg before becoming a curate in Västra Frölunda in 1938. He was also involved in several organizations including the Church Volunteer Corps in Lund, diocesan council in Carl Johans församling, and the Memory Foundation and Association for Seamen's Care in Älvsborg."
